<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bastard2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bastard,</orth> subst., a person born out of wedlock: <cit><quote>if my dear love were but the child of state, it might for Fortune's b. be unfathered,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 124.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 124, 2</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--s of his foul adulterate heart,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 175" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 175</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>getting a hundred --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.125" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 125</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.190" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 190</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.193" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 193</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.79" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.1.215" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 1, 215</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.100" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 100</bibl> <cit><quote>(--s to the English).</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 3, 73</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 3, 73</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.83" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 83</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.207" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 207</bibl> <cit><quote>(a b. to the time).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.93" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 93</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">2, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.42" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.123" default="NO" valid="yes">2, 123</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.5.15" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.70" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 2, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.5.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 5, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 2, 56</bibl> <cit><quote>(--s and syllables of no allowance to your bosom's truth).</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 5.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. V, 4, 2</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 6</bibl> etc. etc.
